    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-02-13T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-02-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="609"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d609">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">150.071 Control/168</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Canadian Legation</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Memorandum</hi>
                </p>
                <p>Bill No. H. R. 3842, “to provide for the deportation of certain alien seamen and
                    for other purposes”, was reported to the House of Representatives by the
                    Committee on Immigration and Naturalization on February 7th 1934. This Bill is
                    identical with measures for the same object which have been introduced in
                    previous Congresses; a similar Bill is pending before the Senate.<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d609fn2">S. 868.</note>
                </p>
                <p>The Canadian Legation desires to direct attention to its memorandum of January
                    27th 1932,<note n="3" xml:id="d609fn3">
                        <ref target="frus1932v01#pg_956">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1932, vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">i</hi>, p. 956</ref>.</note> in which the views of
                    the Government of Canada on this measure were brought to the attention of the
                    Department of State. The terms of this memorandum may be considered as applying
                    to H. R. 3842.</p>
                <closer>
                    <dateline rendition="#left">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-02-13">February 13,
                            1934</date>.</dateline>
                </closer>
            </div>
